cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.AR, cs.PL, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses a new side-channel attack against Intel SGX, which falls under the domain of cryptography and security. 
2. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes a software-based countermeasure to mitigate the branch shadowing attack, which falls under the domain of software engineering. 
3. cs.AR (Architecture) - The paper discusses the architecture of Intel SGX and how the attack exploits a branch-prediction side channel, which falls under the domain of architecture. 
4. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper discusses the control flow of an enclave program running on SGX hardware, which falls under the domain of programming languages. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the execution control of enclave programs and proposes a technique to control the execution in a fine-grained manner, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
